Storyline

Doug Harris (Josh Gad) is a lovable but socially awkward 
groom-to-be with a problem: he has no best man. With less than
 two weeks to go until he marries the girl of his dreams 
(Kaley Cuoco-Sweeting), Doug is referred to Jimmy Callahan 
(Kevin Hart), owner and CEO of Best Man, Inc., a company 
that provides flattering best men for socially challenged guys 
in need. What ensues is a hilarious wedding charade as they 
try to pull off the big con, and an unexpected budding 
bromance between Doug and his fake best man Jimmy.
